  "text": "The proportion of adoption of decision 0 among type-i agents is denoted as x i , while the proportion of adoption of decision 0 among all agents is denoted as x. We call x i the population dynamics of type-i agents and x the population dynamics of the entire network (or simply population dynamics). Obviously, we have x = I i=1 q i x i . Our goal in this letter is to study the steady-state equilibrium of the population dynamics x and show that this equilibrium coincides with the centralized detector [CITATION_1] .",
